    "id_prev": "128.1608",
    "id_next": "128.1611",
    "refcode_1": "AH",
    "refcode_2": "349",
    "refcode_3": "4",
    "refcode_4": "",
    "refcode_short": "AH 349.4",
    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 349.4 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Never let a word of reproach or faultfinding fall upon the ears of your husband. You sometimes pass through strait places, but do not talk of these trials. Silence is eloquence. Hasty speech will only increase your unhappiness. Be cheerful and happy. Bring all the sunshine possible into your home, and shut out the shadows. Let the bright beams of the Sun of Righteousness shine into the chambers of your soul temple. Then the fragrance of the Christian life will be brought into your family. There will be no dwelling upon disagreeable things, which many times have no truth in them.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">2<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 145, 1900\" data-link=\"14065.7646001\">Letter 145, 1900</span>.</span></a></sup>",
